events.comment: Go through each brick and pick a random animation
Check if the device is a mobile device or not
If the example is running on a PC, use the keyboard to control the pad
If the left arrow key is pressed and the pad is not at the left edge of the screen, move the pad left
If the right arrow key is pressed and the pad is not at the right edge of the screen, move the pad right
If the device is a mobile device, use the pointer to move the pad toward the position of the pointer
Move the ball if it stopped

Handle collision with brick:
Each time, we test where is located the ball, and we can it bouncing according to its position
